Program: Discovery
Title: Lifespan - a matter of life and death
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jrytk
Last Broadcast Date: 19 October 2004
Investigation into the diversity of creatures' lifespans, including the Sequoia tree. Why do some living things, such as trees, live for hundreds of years, while others, such as mice, live for a matter of months.